race.comment: IRON MAN (1) resumes and is a noted fresh performer, having held his own in town throughout last campaign. While this trip may be a touch sharp, he draws well and gets weight relief with the claim. Can make a winning return and break a long run of outs. LORDSTER (2) is also first-up and boasts a strong resuming record (2/3), including an impressive Rosehill win last time in. Trialled well and although likely to get back from the draw over a journey shy of his best, he'll be launching late if they overdo it up front. DIS IS HEAVEN (4) closed off nicely into the frame when resuming at Gosford. Strips fitter and draws well. Should be competitive. DE FORZA (12) is going better than his form suggests and has a strong record here. Expect him to put his best foot forward.
